    "questions": [],
    "assumptions": [
      "Feature is a backend-only extension of reliabilitySummary.perModel[modelId]. No GraphQL schema changes; no new DB tables.",
      "Minimum deliverable per plan: add per-scenario matches/trials so Repeatability populates; add perPair section with netPressureRank + winRate + matches/trials + run/condition IDs so Coherence populates.",
      "Underlying numbers are already computed in cloud/apps/api/src/services/analysis/aggregate/variance.ts; this feature surfaces them in the output JSON rather than computing anything new.",
      "Canonical appeal-level mapping for netPressureRank is strongly:+2, somewhat:+1, neutral:0, opponentSomewhat:-1, opponentStrongly:-2, target_appeal - opposing_appeal per Decision 4 in the Consistency report plan.",
      "winRate = (strongly + somewhat) / (sampleCount - neutralCount); fall back to 0 when denominator is 0.",
      "perPair keying is by valueKey; perCondition array is indexed by scenarioId so drill-down deep links can round-trip through the existing condition routing.",
      "Backfill runs the aggregate worker over every AGGREGATE analysis row where status = CURRENT. Replaces the existing analysis rows (supersedes old) and writes new CURRENT. Implemented as a CLI job in cloud/apps/api/src/cli/ reusing the existing worker entrypoint; not a migration.",
      "Backfill is idempotent \u2014 re-running produces the same output (modulo the CURRENT/SUPERSEDED flip on first run).",
      "Consistency report resolver handles the missing fields gracefully today (returns insufficient-coverage rather than crashing); pipeline work is purely additive.",
      "Two PRs: PR1 adds matches/trials (unblocks Repeatability); PR2 adds perPair with netPressureRank/winRate/runIds/conditionIds (unblocks Coherence). Backfill ships with PR2 or immediately after."
    ],
    "summary": "Extend the aggregate analysis pipeline to emit the per-scenario Bernoulli counts and per-pair Coherence ingredients the Models / Consistency report needs. Also ship a backfill script to re-run the aggregate worker on existing CURRENT AGGREGATE analyses. Discovery carried in from the Consistency report PRs (#702, #704, #705).",
